#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Physically secure your server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:8
msgid ""
"Very often people who self-host don't have proper storage for their system. "
"Leaving the server in several parts, in a high traffic area, accessible to "
"children or pets, or in a poorly ventilated area can quickly turn into a "
"disaster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Secure your hard drives"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:12
msgid ""
"Ideally, your hard disks should be fixed to prevent vibrations which can "
"accelerate the wear of the equipment or even reduce its performance, "
"especially if there is another disk next to it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reduce swapiness for SD cards and SSDs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:16
msgid ""
"If you use a swap file with an SSD or SD card with too much swapiness, your "
"storage media could give up the ghost prematurely due to too many writes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:18
msgid "To prevent this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "cat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:24
msgid "If it is above 10:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:25
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sysctl vm.swappiness=10\n"
"nano /etc/sysctl.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:31
msgid ""
"If present, change the vm.swappiness value to 10. Otherwise add the line:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "vm.swappiness = 10\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "Storage redundancy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:39
msgid ""
"In order to limit hardware failures of storage media, it can be relevant to "
"set up a cluster of mirrored disks (RAID, ZFS). The idea here is that "
"everything that is written to one disk will be written to the other. This "
"way, if one fails, the other continues to work and the server is still fully "
"functional."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:41
msgid ""
"There are also more advanced clusters that maximize fault tolerance (failure "
"of 2 disks like RAID6) or storage (see RAID 5)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:43
msgid ""
"However, these disk clustering techniques should not be considered as "
"backups. A RAID array should be considered as a single storage medium. "
"Indeed, if this technique prevents having to reinstall in case of a probable "
"disk crash, it is far from zero risk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:45
msgid ""
"Some examples of situations known to professional system administrators:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:52
msgid ""
"the disks of a cluster mounted with disks of the same brand can fail almost "
"at the same time within a few hours"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:52
msgid ""
"without monitoring the health of the disks, there is a good chance that the "
"failure of one disk in the cluster will only be noticed when a second one "
"fails (\\>\\<)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:52
msgid ""
"if you don't have a spare disk, the delay in purchasing one may result in "
"the other disk crashing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:52
msgid ""
"a half-functional disk that produces errors can propagate its error through "
"the cluster"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:52
msgid ""
"the disk connectors or the RAID controller can also produce errors or fail"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/40.backups/20.avoid_hardware_failure.mdx:52
msgid ""
"the more complex you make the architecture with many components, the more "
"likely it is that one of them will fail"
msgstr ""

